The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs, specifically Node Multiway Cut and Subset Feedback Vertex Set, and focuses on the parameterization by mim-width, which is a measure of the complexity of a graph decomposition. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
